##   Employee Management System

This is a simple **Employee Management System** built using **JAVA Spring Boot** for the backend running on `http://localhost:8080` and a **frontend application** (React) running on `http://localhost:5173`.

##  Features

- Add new employees 
- View all employees 
- Update employee details 
- Delete employees 
- CORS configured to allow frontend communication

##  Tech Stack

- **Backend**: Spring Boot (REST API)
- **Frontend**: React / Vite
- **Data Store**: In-memory (using `HashMap<Long, User>`)

##  API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint        | Description           |
|--------|------------------|-----------------------|
| `GET`  | `/api/users`     | Get all users         |
| `POST` | `/api/users`     | Add a new user        |
| `PUT`  | `/api/users/{id}`| Update a user by ID   |
| `DELETE`| `/api/users/{id}`| Delete a user by ID  |


##   Employee Management System

This is a simple **Employee Management System** built using **JAVA Spring Boot** for the backend running on `http://localhost:8080` and a **frontend application** (React) running on `http://localhost:5173`.

##  Features

- Add new employees 
- View all employees 
- Update employee details 
- Delete employees 
- CORS configured to allow frontend communication

##  Tech Stack

- **Backend**: Spring Boot (REST API)
- **Frontend**: React / Vite
- **Data Store**: In-memory (using `HashMap<Long, User>`)

##  API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint        | Description            |
|--------|------------------|-----------------------|
| `GET`  | `/api/users`     | Get all users         |
| `POST` | `/api/users`     | Add a new user        |
| `PUT`  | `/api/users/{id}`| Update a user by ID   |
| `DELETE`| `/api/users/{id}`| Delete a user by ID  |


## Setup Instructions

## Prerequisites
- Java 17+
- Maven
- Node.js (for frontend)

## Backend Setup (Spring Boot)
-  Navigate into the Backend directory
    cd Backend


-  Build and run the backend
    mvn clean install
    mvn spring-boot:run

##  Frontend Setup (Reactjs)
-  Navigate into the Frontend directory
    cd Frontend

-  Install dependencies
    npm install

-  Run the frontend app
    npm run dev


## Sample Output
-Frontend
1. Adding Employee





